--- Quickstart
0. Install rustup
1. Clone repository
2. Create executable with cargo b --release
3. Create $HOME/aup/root_dir.txt
	It must contain 1 line - the root path to your music folder
	Example: /Users/foobar/Music
4. Run audio_player
	There is 1 optional argument, the start directory, to begin playback immediately
	Example: audio_player <START_DIR_ABSOLUTE_PATH>


--- Keybinds
While picking a song:
Quit				Esc / q
Select previous			k / Up
Select next			j / Down
Select first			g / Home
Select last			G / End
Switch to devices		l
Switch to directories		Tab
Pick song			Enter
Try to reconnect current device	f
Randomize song order		r
Pause				p / Space / F8 / Pause
Skip				s / F9
Mute				m / F10
Decrease volume			v / F11
Increase volume			V / F12
Seek backward 1 second		Left
Seek forward 1 second		Right


While picking a device:
Quit				Esc / q
Select previous			k / Up
Select next			j / Down
Select first			g / Home
Select last			G / End
Switch to song list		h
Pick output device		Enter
Try to reconnect current device	f
Refresh devices			r
Pause				p / Space / F8 / Pause
Skip				s / F9
Mute				m / F10
Decrease volume			v / F11
Increase volume			V / F12


While picking a directory:
Quit			Esc / q
Switch to song list	Tab
Select previous		Up / k
Select next		Down / j
Select first		g
Select last		G
Pick directory		Enter


--- Notes
If you pause playback and resume after a prolonged period of time,
it is highly likely that the output stream for the output device will no longer be active.

Use the keybind 'f' in song/device mode to force rebuilding the output stream for the current output device.
Refreshing devices with 'r' and picking the same device with Enter will not work because the device is cached.

Not all codecs and formats are enabled.
If you want more codecs (adpcm, pcm, vorbis) or formats (aiff, caf, mkv, or wav) then you will need to:

1. Edit Cargo.toml to add the relevant feature flags
	Rodio feature flags (* = enabled)
	* flac
	* mp3
	* mp4
	* symphonia
	* symphonia-ogg
	* libopus
	vorbis
	wav

	symphonia-adpcm
	symphonia-aiff
	symphonia-all
	symphonia-caf
	symphonia-mkv
	symphonia-mp1
	symphonia-mp2
	symphonia-mp3
	symphonia-mpa
	claxon
	hound
	lewton
	minimp3
	wav_output

	Symphonia feature flags (* = enabled)
	all -> all-codecs, all-formats
	all-codecs -> aac, adpcm, alac, flac, mp1, mp2, mp3, pcm, vorbis
	all-formats -> aiff, caf, isomp4, mkv, ogg, wav

	* aac -> symphonia-codec-aac
	adpcm -> symphonia-codec-adpcm
	* alac -> symphonia-codec-alac
	* flac -> symphonia-bundle-flac
	mp1 -> symphonia-bundle-mp3/mp1
	mp2 -> symphonia-bundle-mp3/mp2
	mp3 -> symphonia-bundle-mp3/mp3
	* mpa -> mp1, mp2, mp3
	pcm -> symphonia-codec-pcm
	vorbis -> symphonia-codec-vorbis

	* isomp4 -> symphonia-format-isomp4
	* ogg -> symphonia-format-ogg
	aiff -> symphonia-format-riff/aiff
	caf -> symphonia-format-caf
	mkv -> symphonia-format-mkv
	wav -> symphonia-format-riff/wav


2. Edit the source code
	In the start_playback method of the SongsState struct,
	call codec_registry.register_all() with the desired Decoder


3. Build
	cargo b --release
